Author: iampieman
Text: I posted on my normal Reddit account instead of this account yesterday and didn’t realise for 5 minutes. Kill me.   One time I changed my Instagram account to public for this app, and didn’t realise that led to accepting the 30+ requests I’d left unanswered for years, including previous and current employers/coworkers I didn’t want to see my account. I freaked out, blocked some of the main ones I knew I definitely didn’t want there and then deactivated my account for a while. Smh.
